Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and morphological tagging.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a model using Wsabie, a discriminative embedding-based model with rank-based learning.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with developing accurate natural language processing tools using machine learning techniques.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper proposes a neural network-based approach for morphological tagging.
- cs.DL (Deep Learning) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a deep learning model for morphological tagging.
